- `f_binade_-2`: union `0` / `10`, hard gaps `[95, 96, 101, 102, 103, 104, 106, 107, 108, 110]`.
- `f_binade_le_-3`: union `0` / `50`, hard gaps `[1, 6, 8, 10, 11, 12, 14, 21, 23, 24, 27, 30]`.

## Interpretation

The pair is real on the native Schwarzschild `f_binade_-1` support mask, but it is not yet a stable route-selection law. Neighboring native masks do not inherit the half-grid coverage, and one-ULP coordinate perturbations change the direct gap set and companion coverage enough to break full resolution.

This narrows the next investigation: the useful object is not simply the route pair. The missing ingredient is a guard or predictor that identifies when the native `f_binade_-1` partition is in the route-pair basin and when coordinate-level perturbations move the read outside it.

